// Airbnb JavaScript Style Guide ‚Äî `no-continue`: don't use `continue`; it can
// hurt readability of the control flow. This covers both the plain
// `continue;` and the labeled form `continue label;` ‚Äî the `JsContinueStatement`
// node matches both. A bare `` `continue` `` backtick snippet does NOT compile
// as an expression in Biome 2.4.16, so the node-kind pattern is used here.
// `break` and normal loop bodies are left alone.
language js

JsContinueStatement() as $node where {
  register_diagnostic(span=$node, message="Do not use `continue`; refactor the loop's control flow (e.g. invert the condition) instead.", severity="warn")
}
